Alex wrote:

&gt; Thanks for the insight, I was using 1.4.0 which didn&#39;t include
&gt; checkpointing. 
&gt;
&gt; Is it possible to configure the job to automatically save checkpoints for
&gt; every say 10 minutes or 500 pages?  

No.  Not yet.  You think this should be part of the crawler?  Or is it 
ok if its done by an external process?  It can be done from cron via the 
cmdline-jmxclient -- See http://crawler.archive.org/cmdline-jmxclient/ 
-- or from another java process with its own scheduling mechanism 
perhaps based on JMX timer MBeans (The alternative is adding scheduling 
support to Heritrix -- screens and API and database of scheduled tasks, 
etc.).

&gt; I didn&#39;t see this option available, so I
&gt; assume I would have to call this programmatically in a specialized
&gt; processor.  

&gt; Now in order to save checkpoint in the UI you must pause the
&gt; job.  Can you do this in a processor while the job is running?
&gt;
Thats right.  Its a bit of a pain at the moment.  Checkpointing should 
manage the pause, checkpoint, resume cycle itself (There&#39;s an RFE to do 
this here: &#39;[ 1302207 ] unattended checkpointing&#39; 
http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1302207&group_id=73833&atid=539102).  
Better would be doing away with need for pause.

